Definition.WordDefinition:
Eastern \East"ern\, a. [AS. e['a]stern.] 1. Situated or dwelling in the east; oriental; as, an eastern gate; Eastern countries. [1913 Webster]
Eastern churches first did Christ embrace. --Stirling. [1913 Webster]
2. Going toward the east, or in the direction of east; as, an eastern voyage. [1913 Webster]

eastern adj 1: lying toward or situated in the east; "the eastern end of the island" 2: of or characteristic of eastern regions of the United States; "the Eastern establishment" [ant: {western}] 3: lying in or toward the east; "the east side of NY"; "eastern cities" [syn: {easterly}] 4: relating to or characteristic of regions of eastern parts of the world; "the Eastern Hemisphere"; "Eastern Europe"; "the Eastern religions" [ant: {western}] 5: from the east; used especially of winds; "an east wind"; "the winds are easterly" [syn: {easterly}]
